Set 3 
Create Employee and Department table  by identifying Primary key and  foreign keys and solve the 
following queries 
Employee (emp_id, emp_name, city, salary, department) 
Department (dept_id, dept_name, location) 
1. Display schema of each table.in each table. 
2. Insert 10 records in each table 
3. Insert a new department into the Department table. 
4. Insert an employee record without specifying the salary column. 
5. Update the salary of all employees by adding 20% increment. 
6. Display employee name and annual salary of employees whose names having the second letter e. 
7. Update the city to 'Pune' for employees working in the 'IT' department. 

CREATE TABLE Department (
    dept_id NUMBER PRIMARY KEY,
    dept_name VARCHAR2(20),
    location VARCHAR2(20)
);
CREATE TABLE Employee (
    emp_id NUMBER PRIMARY KEY,
    emp_name VARCHAR2(20),
    city VARCHAR2(20),
    salary NUMBER,
    department NUMBER,
    FOREIGN KEY (department) REFERENCES Department(dept_id)
);
DESC Department;
DESC Employee;
